 GIN - golang web framework:

Source: https://github.com/gin-gonic/gin#contents

1.) gin.H refers to the map[string]interface{} . We create maps in json using gin.H

2.)Context is the most important part of gin. It allows us to pass variables between middleware, 
   // manage the flow, validate the JSON of a request and render a JSON response for example. ... 
   // Errors is a list of errors attached to all the handlers/middlewares who used this context.
3.)gin Context -> Param is used for parameters in api path (path parameters).
               ->Query is used for query parameter. (Query parameters)
               ->PostForm is used to post formdata

